{
  "answer": "**Yama Smṛti, Chapter 2** prescribes these fourfold-value (*caturguṇa*) fines for the specified grocery adulterations in two consecutive verses (YSS 2.37–38).[^1][^2]\n\n> Ghee sold mixed with sesame oil under the name of ghee, / the merchant shall be made to pay four times the value; or oil mixed with ghee. // YSS_2.37 //\n\n> Pepper with stone fragments, salt with earth, / and asafoetida with tree resin—he shall likewise be made to pay four times the value. // YSS_2.38 //\n\n[^1]: Yama Smṛti, [p-551495](/works/unknown-yama-smrti-552f8d/02/translation/#p-551495).\n\n[^2]: Yama Smṛti, [p-6039eb](/works/unknown-yama-smrti-552f8d/02/translation/#p-6039eb).",
